Add
Use git add to put file to staging area.


git add &lt;filename&gt;

We say that this file has been staged. Check to see what happened:

git status &lt;filename&gt;

git add
Use git add to put file to staging area.


git add &lt;filename&gt;

We say that this file has been staged. * git add .: new + modifiled files, does not stage deletions: Scope: Current dir only * git add -A: new + modified + deletions. Scope: Entire repo.

git status &lt;filename&gt;
